{
  "question_id": "c57268b8-ddfb-4ea0-837f-5256d9323f19",
  "short_text": "Numbers in Hollow Pyramid",
  "content": "Given a number `N`, write a program to print a **Hollow Pyramid** of `N` rows using numbers starting from **5**.\n\n```\n    5\n   5 6\n  5   7\n 5     8\n5 6 7 8 9\n\n```\n\n<MultiLineNote>\nThere is a space after every number.\n</MultiLineNote>\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` rows containing numbers starting from **5** as a **Hollow Pyramid** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 5`,\n\n- Print the numbers on **5** rows as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/cx-numbers-in-hollow-pyramid.png' widthPercent='70'/>\n\n<MultiLineNote>\n\nIn the given image,\n\n- The Empty box indicates a space (\" \").\n- The Number in the box indicates the number and a space (\"5 \").\n\n</MultiLineNote>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n    5\n   5 6\n  5   7\n 5     8\n5 6 7 8 9\n\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "f80ffcea-a56c-43b0-bd85-14f3b6adaabc",
      "code_content": "n = int(input())\n\nfor i in range(1, n):\n\n    left_spaces = n - i\n    middle_spaces = (2 * n - 1) - ( (2 * left_spaces) + 2 )\n    \n    if i == 1:\n        print(\" \"*left_spaces + \"5\")\n    else:\n        print(\" \"*left_spaces + \"5\" + \" \"*middle_spaces + str(5 + i - 1))\n\nfinal_line = \"\"\n\nfor j in range(n):\n\n    final_line += str(5 + j) + \" \"\n\nprint(final_line)\n",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
